It doesn't bother me either way. The reason for which revision was sought is shifty and I imagine conservatives will have a field day with this guy. IMO he deserves whatever verbal criticism they dish out for mocking the sincerity with which such lawsuits should be pursued.<br>
<br>
I don't know how much time and people energy it would take to return the pledge to its original form. I'd guess not a lot. I'm worried about people like Varro using the victory as a means to call other inconsistencies out and demand that all references to god be erased from public view, from government life. At that point I'd rather taxes, if any monies is used to accommodate such people, to go to something else. Like the budget deficit, or a tax break for affordable housing. I'd rather money be used to include as many as possible without rearranging the world to fit someone's universe.<br>
